      moduleKey: "foundations",
      kicker: "Foundations",
      dek: `There's an old saying that casting is 90% of directing. It's not quite literal, but it points at a truth every experienced director knows: the biggest lever you have over performance isn't a note on set — it's who you put in the role in the first place. Cast right, and directing gets easy. Cast wrong, and no technique will save you.`,
